text: Siege of Acre may refer to: *Siege of Acre (1104) – following the First Crusade *Siege of Acre (1189–1191) – during the Third Crusade *Siege of Acre (1263) – Baibars laid siege to the Crusader city, but abandoned it to attack Nazareth. *Siege of Acre (1291) – Fall of the final Crusader city in the Levant *Siege of Acre (1799) – during the French Revolutionary Wars *Siege of Acre (1821) – part of Ottoman power struggles *Siege of Acre (1832) – by Ibrahim Pasha of Egypt ==See also== * Battle of Acre (disambiguation)
title: Siege of Acre
